<div class="card" id="Top">
    <div class="card-header bg-dark text-light">Level 2</div>
    <div class="card-body">
        <p>Using the SportsORM, complete all the following queries and show their results on Level2.cshtml.</p>
        <ol>
            <li><a href="#1">...all teams in the Atlantic Soccer Conference</a></li>
            <li><a href="#2">...all (current) players on the Boston Penguins (Hint: Boston is the Location, Penguins is the TeamName)</a></li>
            <li><a href="#3">...all (current) players in the International Collegiate Baseball Conference</a></li>
            <li><a href="#4">...all (current) players in the American Conference of Amateur Football with last name "Lopez"</a></li>
            <li><a href="#5">...all football players</a></li>
            <li><a href="#6">...all teams with a (current) player named "Sophia"</a></li>
            <li><a href="#7">...all leagues with a (current) player named "Sophia"</a></li>
            <li><a href="#8">...everyone with the last name "Flores" who DOESN'T (currently) play for the Washington Roughriders</a></li>
        </ol>
    </div>
</div>

<h4>To make navigation easier links have been added to top of page as well as to each task</h4>    

<div class="col-sm-6" id="1">
    <div class="card">
        <div class="card-body">
            <a href="#Top"><h3>All Teams in the Atlantic Soccer Conference</h3></a>
            <table class="table table-striped">
                <tr>
                    <th>Name</th>
                    <th>League</th>
                    <th>Sport</th>
                </tr>
                @foreach(var l in ViewBag.Atlantic)
                {
                    <tr>
                        <td>@l.TeamName</td>
                        <td>@l.CurrLeague.Name</td>
                        <td>@l.CurrLeague.Sport</td>
                    </tr>
                }
            </table>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

